library(shiny)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(bulkAnalyseR)

r.files <- list.files(path = getwd(), pattern = '\\.R$')
r.files <- setdiff(r.files, 'app.R')
for(fl in r.files) source(fl)
rda.files <- list.files(pattern = '\\.rda$')
for(fl in rda.files) load(fl)
anno <- list()
anno[[1]] <- data.frame(
ENSEMBL = rownames(expression.matrix[[1]]),
NAME = rownames(expression.matrix[[1]])
)

ui <- function(request){
navbarPage(
'Visualization of RNAseq from human BC, App created by Nuno S. OsÃ³rio on 26-10-2023. PI: Fernando Rodrigues',
theme = shinythemes::shinytheme('flatly'),
header = tags$head(tags$style('body {overflow-y: scroll;}')),
footer = bookmarkButton(),
tabPanel(
title = 'RNA',
modalityPanelUI(
id = 'RNA',
metadata = metadata[[1]],
organism = 'hsapiens',
panels.default = c('SampleSelect', 'QC', 'GRN', 'DE', 'DEplot', 'DEsummary', 'Enrichment', 'GRNenrichment', 'Cross', 'Patterns')
),
),
)
}

server <- function(input, output, session){
modalityPanelServer(
id = 'RNA',
expression.matrix = expression.matrix[[1]],
metadata = metadata[[1]],
anno = anno[[1]],
organism = 'hsapiens',
panels.default = c('SampleSelect', 'QC', 'GRN', 'DE', 'DEplot', 'DEsummary', 'Enrichment', 'GRNenrichment', 'Cross', 'Patterns')
)
}

shinyApp(ui, server, enableBookmarking = 'url')
